1. Figma File Organization (Do this first)
Layer naming convention — use this exactly:
Screen / Component / Variant
Examples:
  Feed / PostCard / Default
  Feed / PostCard / WithImage
  Feed / PostCard / Dark
  Global / BottomNav / Light
  Global / BottomNav / Dark
  Auth / InputField / Empty
  Auth / InputField / Filled
  Auth / InputField / Error
Grouping checklist before handoff:

Every screen is its own Figma frame, named clearly (01-Login, 02-Feed, etc.)
Reusable elements (buttons, inputs, nav bar) are components, not flat shapes
All colors use your local Figma color styles (not hardcoded fills)
All text uses Figma text styles (Heading/24, Body/15, Label/13, etc.)
No hidden or orphan layers sitting outside frames


